<h3 class="date"><a href="/2009/may/18/">&#x27a0;</a> May 18, 2009</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="usability-passwords" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.baekdal.com/articles/Usability/password-security-usability/">The Usability of Passwords</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>&#8220;It is 10 times more secure to use &#8220;this is fun&#8221; as your password, than &#8220;J4fS&lt;2&#8221;.&#8221;  True dat.  Of course, password complexity isn&#8217;t really an issue.  Easiest way to crack a user&#8217;s password?  Hack a website (or social engineer someone that works for a website) that stores passwords in cleartext.</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
                    Filed under
                    
                        : <a rel="tag" class="tag" href="/tag/passwords/">passwords</a>
                    
